<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="952" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6961.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>150. I think it proper in view of sensational newspaper reports to the
                            contrary, to advise the Department that there is perfect accord between
                            General Díaz and the Provisional President.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>